          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-4-1581514508750-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>While the vegetables are cooking, combine the <strong>soy sauce</strong> and<strong> rice vinegar</strong> with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong> – this is your <strong>stir-fry sauce</strong></p><p>Trim, then slice the <strong>spring onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1581514514856-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1581514514856-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1581514514856-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1581514514856-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-5-1581514514856-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the veg has softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and<strong> ginger</strong> and cook for 1 min, then transfer everything to the pot with the <strong>drained noodles</strong>, reserve the pan</p><p>Return the reserved pan to a high heat with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong>, then pat the <strong>haddock bites </strong>dry with kitchen paper</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>haddock bites </strong>(unevenly sized haddock bites? Chop any larger ones into bite-sized pieces!)<strong> </strong>with a grind of <strong>black pepper</strong> and cook for 1-2 min on each side or until cooked through</p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-6-1581514520103-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
